referenceAnswer:
Add an `ignore` flag in the effect and check it before calling `setUser`:

```js
useEffect(() => {
  let ignore = false;
  fetch(`/api/users/${userId}`)
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(data => { if (!ignore) setUser(data); });
  return () => { ignore = true; };
}, [userId]);
```

Alternatively, use an `AbortController` to cancel the in-flight request on cleanup.

